{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id773f8866-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s407b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"407b"},"text":"§ 407b.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Applicability of Federal Power Act","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The provisions of the Federal Power Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s791a"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 791a","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] shall not apply to or extend over the land by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s407"},"text":"section 407 of this title","children":[],"tail":" or hereafter reserved and dedicated as the Carlsbad Caverns National Park."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id773f8867-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1930-05-14/ch272/s3"},"text":"May 14, 1930, ch. 272, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/46/279"},"text":"46 Stat. 279","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id773f8868-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id773f8869-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id773f886a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal Power Act, referred to in text, was in the original the “Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1920-06-10"},"text":"June 10, 1920","children":[],"tail":", known as the Federal Water Power Act,” and was redesignated as the Federal Power Act by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s791a"},"text":"section 791a of this title","children":[],"tail":". The Federal Power Act is "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1920-06-10/ch285"},"text":"act June 10, 1920, ch. 285","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/41/1063"},"text":"41 Stat. 1063","children":[],"tail":", and is classified generally to chapter 12 (§ 791aet seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s791a"},"text":"section 791a of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
